03/04/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- In an article published in the weekend edition of the Danas newspaper, US Ambassador to Serbia-Montenegro Michael Polt reiterated that any solution to the Kosovo status negotiations must result from compromise. The future solution must strengthen regional stability and guarantee the protection of rights for all Kosovo citizens, he said.
In related news, Slobodan Samardzic, a member of the Serbian negotiating team, called on Sunday (2 April) for a general agreement providing guarantees for the Kosovo Serb community's rights. A third round of direct talks between representatives from Belgrade and Pristina was due to take place Monday in Vienna. (RTS - 02/04/06; Danas, Tanjug - 01/04/06)
